  m_Name: Tibia_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Tibia_R
  partName: Tibia Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right tibia is the primary weight-bearing bone of the canine lower hindlimb,
    extending from the stifle joint to the hock region. It supports body weight during
    standing, walking, running, and jumping activities while providing attachment
    sites for important muscles and ligaments controlling hindlimb movement.
  - The tibia articulates with the femur proximally and the tarsal bones distally,
    contributing to stable and coordinated locomotion. Its strong structure enables
    efficient force transmission and shock absorption throughout the hindlimb.
